  "texts": [
    "Chen et al.",
    "50 performed high-temperature high-pressure MD simulations with ReaxFF 40, 42 to predict the mechanisms and kinetics of several fuel additives, including ethanol, 2-butanol and methyl tert-butyl ether (MTBE).",
    "According to their results, 2-butanol was the best fuel additive at enhancing ignition while MTBE demonstrated similar ignition enhancement to 2-butanol.",
    "By contrast, ethanol was the worst fuel additive, having a negligible effect on the O 2 consumption rate and ignition delay time (IDT) compared with the clean biofuel.",
    "To validate the reliability of ANI-1xnr for simulating biodiesel and to investigate the reported ignition enhancement of fuel additives, we reproduced four systems simulated by Chen et al."
  ],
